{"title_page": "Kar\u00e1d", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| official_name          = Kar\u00e1d\n| other_name             = {{lang|hr|Karadin}} {{in lang|hr}}\n| settlement_type        = Village\n| image                  = Kar\u00e1d l\u00e1tk\u00e9pe a sz\u0151l\u0151hegyr\u0151l.jpg\n| image_caption          = View of the village from the vineyard hill\n|image_shield            = Coa_Hungary_Town_Kar\u00e1d.svg\n| timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset             = +1\n| timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST         = +2\n| map                    = [[File:SomogyMegye.png|center|thumb|275px|Location of Somogy county in Hungary]]\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Hungary|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Southern Transdanubia]]\n| subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name2      = [[Somogy County|Somogy]]\n| subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Hungary|District]]\n| subdivision_name3      = [[Fony\u00f3d District|Fony\u00f3d]]\n| subdivision_type4      = [[List of Catholic dioceses in Hungary|RC Diocese]]\n| subdivision_name4      = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kaposv\u00e1r|Kaposv\u00e1r]]\n| area_total_km2         = 52.38\n| population_total       = 1489<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/apps/hntr.telepules?p_lang=EN&p_id=05263 Kar\u00e1d, KSH]</ref>\n| population_as_of       = 2017\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_demonym     = kar\u00e1di\n| postal_code_type       = [[Postal code]]\n| postal_code            = 8676\n| area_code              = (+36) 84\n| blank4_name_sec1       = [[NUTS statistical regions of Hungary|NUTS 3 code]]\n| blank4_info_sec1       = HU232\n| blank5_name_sec2       = [[List of members of the National Assembly of Hungary (2018\u201322)|MP]]\n| blank5_info_sec2       = [[Mih\u00e1ly Witzmann]] ([[Fidesz]])\n| pushpin_map            = Hungary \n| pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Kar\u00e1d\n| pushpin_mapsize        = \n| coordinates            = {{coord|46.69194|17.84329|region:HU|display=inline,title}}\n| blank_name             = [[Patron Saint]]\n| blank_info             = [[Ladislaus I of Hungary|Ladislaus I]]\n| website                = {{URL|http://www.karad.hu|Kar\u00e1d Online}}\n}}\n\n'''Kar\u00e1d''' ({{lang-hr|Karadin}}) is a village in [[Somogy County|Somogy]] county, [[Hungary]].\n\nThe settlement is part of the [[Balatonbogl\u00e1r wine region]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160410182214/http://www.delbalatonibor.hu/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/HK-Tan%C3%A1cs-Alapszab%C3%A1ly.pdf  A Balatonbogl\u00e1ri borvid\u00e9k hegyk\u00f6zs\u00e9gi tan\u00e1cs\u00e1nak alapszab\u00e1lya (PDF)]</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\nIts name derives from the [[Turkish language|Turkish]] person name, ''Kara'' ({{lang-hu|fekete}}, {{lang-en|black}}). He could be the first owner of the settlement. The same applies to [[K\u00e1ra]].<ref>[http://somogy.hu/publikaciok/kiraly-lajos-somogyi-helysegnevek-nepi-es.html Lajos Kir\u00e1ly : Somogyi helys\u00e9gnevek n\u00e9pi \u00e9s ...]</ref>\n\n==History==\nAccording to ''L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Szita'' the settlement was completely Hungarian in the 18th century.<ref>[https://library.hungaricana.hu/hu/view/SOMM_SomAlm_052/?pg=10&layout=s&query=korp\u00e1d L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Szita : Somogy megyei nemzetis\u00e9gek telep\u00fcl\u00e9st\u00f6rt\u00e9nete a XVIII-XIX. sz\u00e1zadban - Somogyi Almanach 52. (Kaposv\u00e1r, 1993)]</ref>\n\n==Culture==\nThe Hungarian folk songs [[:hu:F\u00f3t h\u00e1t\u00e1n f\u00f3t, egy \u00fcng\u00f6m v\u00f3t|F\u00f3t h\u00e1t\u00e1n f\u00f3t, egy \u00fcng\u00f6m v\u00f3t]] (in 1938) and [[:hu:A kar\u00e1di faluv\u00e9gen|A kar\u00e1di faluv\u00e9gen]] (in 1933) were collected in Kar\u00e1d by [[Gyula D\u00e1vid]] as well as [[:hu:R\u00e9n a b\u00e1r\u00e1ny|R\u00e9n a b\u00e1r\u00e1ny]] (in 1953) by ''L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Vik\u00e1r''.\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.terkepcentrum.hu/index.asp?go=map&tid=5263 Street map (Hungarian)]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Fony\u00f3d District}}\n{{Somogy}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karad}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Somogy County]]\n\n\n{{Somogy-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| official_name          = Kar\u00e1d\n| other_name             = {{lang|hr|Karadin}} {{in lang|hr}}\n| settlement_type        = Village\n| image                  = Kar\u00e1d l\u00e1tk\u00e9pe a sz\u0151l\u0151hegyr\u0151l.jpg\n| image_caption          = View of the village from the vineyard hill\n|image_shield            = Coa_Hungary_Town_Kar\u00e1d.svg\n| timezone               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset             = +1\n| timezone_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST         = +2\n| map                    = [[File:SomogyMegye.png|center|thumb|275px|Location of Somogy county in Hungary]]\n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Hungary|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Southern Transdanubia]]\n| subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name2      = [[Somogy County|Somogy]]\n| subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Hungary|District]]\n| subdivision_name3      = [[Fony\u00f3d District|Fony\u00f3d]]\n| subdivision_type4      = [[List of Catholic dioceses in Hungary|RC Diocese]]\n| subdivision_name4      = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Kaposv\u00e1r|Kaposv\u00e1r]]\n| area_total_km2         = 52.38\n| population_total       = 1489<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/apps/hntr.telepules?p_lang=EN&p_id=05263 Kar\u00e1d, KSH]</ref>\n| population_as_of       = 2017\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_demonym     = kar\u00e1di\n| postal_code_type       = [[Postal code]]\n| postal_code            = 8676\n| area_code              = (+36) 84\n| blank4_name_sec1       = [[NUTS statistical regions of Hungary|NUTS 3 code]]\n| blank4_info_sec1       = HU232\n| blank5_name_sec2       = [[List of members of the National Assembly of Hungary (2018\u201322)|MP]]\n| blank5_info_sec2       = [[Mih\u00e1ly Witzmann]] ([[Fidesz]])\n| pushpin_map            = Hungary \n| pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_caption    = Location of Kar\u00e1d\n| pushpin_mapsize        = \n| coordinates            = {{coord|46.69194|17.84329|region:HU|display=inline,title}}\n| blank_name             = [[Patron Saint]]\n| blank_info             = [[Ladislaus I of Hungary|Ladislaus I]]\n| website                = {{URL|http://www.karad.hu|Kar\u00e1d Online}}\n}}\n\n'''Kar\u00e1d''' ({{lang-hr|Karadin}}) is a village in [[Somogy County|Somogy]] county, [[Hungary]].\n\nThe settlement is part of the [[Balatonbogl\u00e1r wine region]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20160410182214/http://www.delbalatonibor.hu/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/HK-Tan%C3%A1cs-Alapszab%C3%A1ly.pdf  A Balatonbogl\u00e1ri borvid\u00e9k hegyk\u00f6zs\u00e9gi tan\u00e1cs\u00e1nak alapszab\u00e1lya (PDF)]</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\nIts name derives from the [[Turkish language|Turkish]] person name, ''Kara'' ({{lang-hu|fekete}}, {{lang-en|black}}). He could be the first owner of the settlement. The same applies to [[K\u00e1ra]].<ref>[http://somogy.hu/publikaciok/kiraly-lajos-somogyi-helysegnevek-nepi-es.html Lajos Kir\u00e1ly : Somogyi helys\u00e9gnevek n\u00e9pi \u00e9s ...]</ref>\n\n==History==\nAccording to ''L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Szita'' the settlement was completely Hungarian in the 18th century.<ref>[https://library.hungaricana.hu/hu/view/SOMM_SomAlm_052/?pg=10&layout=s&query=korp\u00e1d L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Szita : Somogy megyei nemzetis\u00e9gek telep\u00fcl\u00e9st\u00f6rt\u00e9nete a XVIII-XIX. sz\u00e1zadban - Somogyi Almanach 52. (Kaposv\u00e1r, 1993)]</ref>\n\n==Culture==\nThe Hungarian folk songs [[:hu:F\u00f3t h\u00e1t\u00e1n f\u00f3t, egy \u00fcng\u00f6m v\u00f3t|F\u00f3t h\u00e1t\u00e1n f\u00f3t, egy \u00fcng\u00f6m v\u00f3t]] (in 1938) and [[:hu:A kar\u00e1di faluv\u00e9gen|A kar\u00e1di faluv\u00e9gen]] (in 1933) were collected in Kar\u00e1d by [[Gyula D\u00e1vid]] as well as [[:hu:R\u00e9n a b\u00e1r\u00e1ny|R\u00e9n a b\u00e1r\u00e1ny]] (in 1953) by ''L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Vik\u00e1r''.\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.terkepcentrum.hu/index.asp?go=map&tid=5263 Street map (Hungarian)]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Somogy-geo-stub}}\n\n{{Fony\u00f3d District}}\n{{Somogy}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Karad}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Somogy County]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kar%C3%A1d"}
{"title_page": "Kartitsch", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Kartitsch\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = Kartitsch.jpg\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = AUT Kartitsch COA.svg\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = Kartitsch.png\n| mapsize             = 260x260px\n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Lienz district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|46|43|00|N|12|29|00|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Tyrol (state)|Tyrol]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Lienz District|Lienz]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Alois Klammer\n| leader_party  = \n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 1353\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|LZ]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 9941\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 04848\n| website   = [http://www.kartitsch.at www.kartitsch.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Kartitsch''' is a municipality in the district of [[Lienz (district)|Lienz]] in the [[Austria]]n stateof [[state of Tyrol|Tyrol]].\n\n==Geography==\nKartitsch lies on both sides of the [[Gail River]], near its confluence with the [[Puster Valley]]. The municipal area of Kartitsch is bounded in the north of the western foothills of the Lienzer Dolomites and to the south of the [[Carnic Alps]], which contains the border with [[Italy]]. The municipality contains villages, such as Sankt Oswald. It lies near other Austrian municipalities, such as [[Abfaltersbach]], [[Anras]], [[Heinfels]], [[Obertilliach]], [[Sillian]], and [[Strassen, Austria|Strassen]].\n\n==Population==\n{{Historical populations\n|align=left\n|1971|1002\n|1981|1006\n|1991|922\n|2001|897\n}}\n\n==Coat of arms==\nThe coat of arms of the Kartitsch is a rising golden crescent on a blue field. In 1465, the [[Frederick III, Holy Roman Emperor]], awarded the coat of arms to [[Hans Wiser|Hans]] and [[Jacob Wiser]], leading men of the municipality.\n\n==Tourism==\nBoth tourism and agriculture form the basis of the local economy. In 2003, Kartitsch had 84,000 visitor-nights. Local points of interest include:\n*The Parish Church of St. Leonhard: a Gothic church completed in 1479, with a high altar from the years 1761\u20131763.\n*The 'Our Lady' Church: built in 1680 to 1685, one of the notable early Baroque churches in the area. The stucco frames came from the workshop of Gallus Apeller in Innsbruck. The Church is located in [[Hollbruck]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Lienz (district)}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Lienz District]]\n\n\n{{Tyrol-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Kartitsch\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = Kartitsch.jpg\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = AUT Kartitsch COA.svg\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = Kartitsch.png\n| mapsize             = 260x260px\n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Lienz district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|46|43|00|N|12|29|00|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Tyrol (state)|Tyrol]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Lienz District|Lienz]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Alois Klammer\n| leader_party  = \n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 1353\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|LZ]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 9941\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 04848\n| website   = [http://www.kartitsch.at www.kartitsch.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Kartitsch''' is a municipality in the district of [[Lienz (district)|Lienz]] in the [[Austria]]n stateof [[state of Tyrol|Tyrol]].\n\n==Geography==\nKartitsch lies on both sides of the [[Gail River]], near its confluence with the [[Puster Valley]]. The municipal area of Kartitsch is bounded in the north of the western foothills of the Lienzer Dolomites and to the south of the [[Carnic Alps]], which contains the border with [[Italy]]. The municipality contains villages, such as Sankt Oswald. It lies near other Austrian municipalities, such as [[Abfaltersbach]], [[Anras]], [[Heinfels]], [[Obertilliach]], [[Sillian]], and [[Strassen, Austria|Strassen]].\n\n==Population==\n{{Historical populations\n|align=left\n|1971|1002\n|1981|1006\n|1991|922\n|2001|897\n}}\n\n==Coat of arms==\nThe coat of arms of the Kartitsch is a rising golden crescent on a blue field. In 1465, the [[Frederick III, Holy Roman Emperor]], awarded the coat of arms to [[Hans Wiser|Hans]] and [[Jacob Wiser]], leading men of the municipality.\n\n==Tourism==\nBoth tourism and agriculture form the basis of the local economy. In 2003, Kartitsch had 84,000 visitor-nights. Local points of interest include:\n*The Parish Church of St. Leonhard: a Gothic church completed in 1479, with a high altar from the years 1761\u20131763.\n*The 'Our Lady' Church: built in 1680 to 1685, one of the notable early Baroque churches in the area. The stucco frames came from the workshop of Gallus Apeller in Innsbruck. The Church is located in [[Hollbruck]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat}}\n\n{{Cities and towns in Lienz (district)}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Lienz District]]\n\n\n{{Tyrol-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kartitsch"}
